<br>
&quot;Yasoo! Welcome to Sarmatia, glad to have you in our tribe. Feeling better? A trip to Hades Throne Room doesn't always leave people in high spirits.&quot;<br>
<br>
She laughed a little. No matter what, she could never manage to make her greeting short. Like Queen Hippolyte had once said, she could talk for days. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tiger4157>Tiger4157</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(1/4/01 9:43:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New to Sarmatia</span><hr size=1> ::looks to Gabrielle and smiles with a chuckle:: <br>
<br>
&quot;Yasoo. Thank you. And, yes, I am feeling better. Hades is no fun anymore. In the old times, he at least used to play a few cat-and-mouse games. Now, he just likes to annoy his victims.&quot;<br>
<br>
::grins. yes, this one could talk alright, but Sartha never minded a good conversation:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxvgabriellebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XvGabrielleBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Bard</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(1/5/01 6:07:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New to Sarmatia</span><hr size=1> Gabrielle chuckled lightly as she leaned against her staff. She too always enjoyed a good conversation. As great as Xena was, she was never one for many words. She, on the other hand, would talk to months on end if possible.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah.. you'd think he'd be more grateful after Xena and I recaptured that dead guy who stole his magic helmet.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tiger4157>Tiger4157</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(1/6/01 5:12:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New to Sarmatia</span><hr size=1> ::nods::<br>
<br>
&quot;Indeed, he should be. But that's Hades for ya. I suppose that's why we're here though- to spruce things up a bit when we die. Hades needs a bit of excitement in that droll life of his.&quot;<br>
<br>
::she chuckles lightly and looks to the sky::<br>
<br>
&quot;Then, there's the other male Gods...&quot; <br>
<br>
